dc:description: Blue-green glass unguentarium with almost completely flattened outsplayed body. Very long cylindrical neck ends in widely flared, flattened, ridged rim. Base is slightly concave with pontil mark. Beautifully intact vessel. Very slight tooling at base of neck. Bubbles throughout. Flecks of enamel-like weathering on neck, base. Greenish weathering on underside of rim.
